## Frequently Asked Questions

**Q: I'm a freelancer tracking personal finances. Do I need a commercial license?**  
A: No, if you're tracking your personal finances, the free MIT license applies.

**Q: I'm a freelancer tracking business finances. Do I need a commercial license?**  
A: Yes, any business use requires a commercial license.

**Q: Can I try it before buying a commercial license?**  
A: Yes! You can use the MIT license for evaluation purposes for up to 30 days.

**Q: Can I modify the software under the commercial license?**  
A: Yes, for internal use only. You cannot redistribute modified versions.

**Q: What happens if I violate the license terms?**  
A: License violation may result in immediate termination and legal action.

**Q: Can non-profits use it for free?**  
A: Non-profits must obtain a commercial license but receive a 50% discount.

